# Backend Authentication Configuration Example
# =============================================
# Copy this file to .env and set your demo account passwords
#
# SECURITY WARNING: These are DEMO credentials only!
# In production:
# 1. Use proper user database (PostgreSQL/QuestDB)
# 2. Store password hashes (bcrypt/argon2), NEVER plain text
# 3. Remove demo accounts entirely
# 4. Implement proper user management

# Demo Account Credentials
# For development/testing, you can use the original simple passwords:
DEMO_PASSWORD=demo123
TRADER_PASSWORD=trader123
PREMIUM_PASSWORD=premium123

# Admin Account
# Set to 'supersecret' to match E2E test expectations
# Or use your own secure password
ADMIN_PASSWORD=supersecret

# Note: Backend automatically loads .env via load_dotenv() in src/core/config.py:10
# Restart the backend after modifying .env for changes to take effect

# If .env is not set, the system uses these defaults (with security warnings):
# - DEMO_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_DEMO123
# - TRADER_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_TRADER123
# - PREMIUM_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_PREMIUM123
# - ADMIN_PASSWORD=CHANGE_ME_ADMIN123
